title: [BUG] ImportError: DLL load failed while importing mrseql: The specified module could not be found
body:
**Describe the bug**
<!--
A clear and concise description of what the bug is.
-->
Hello.
I installed SKTime version 0.4.3 on my local Anaconda environment.
When I try to follow 03_classification_multivariate (version 0.4.3) example there is an error from the line:
"from sktime.classification.shapelet_based import MrSEQLClassifier"
Thank you.

**To Reproduce**
<!--
Add a Minimal, Complete, and Verifiable example (for more details, see e.g. https://stackoverflow.com/help/mcve

If the code is too long, feel free to put it in a public gist and link it in the issue: https://gist.github.com
-->

Following the example from 
sktime.org/en/v0.4.3/examples/03_classification_multivariate.html
```python

from sktime.classification.shapelet_based import MrSEQLClassifier

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "ex_multiivariateTSClassification1.py", line 22, in <module>
    from sktime.classification.shapelet_based import MrSEQLClassifier
  File "C:\Users\mee\AppData\Local\Continuum\anaconda3\envs\Python38-TimeSeries\lib\site-packages\sktime\classification\shapelet_based\__init__.py", line 6, in <module>
    from sktime.classification.shapelet_based.mrseql.mrseql import \
ImportError: DLL load failed while importing mrseql: The specified module could not be found.

```

**Expected behavior**
<!--
A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.
-->

**Additional context**
<!--
Add any other context about the problem here.
-->
